Program: The Forum
Title: Unintended Consequences
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p02d5qfp
Last Broadcast Date: Tue 9 Dec 2014
What role does our imagination play in taking us down paths we do not expect? And how far does an artist relinquish control with a work of art? Bridget Kendall asks the poet Peter Anderson, the novelist James Friel and the philosopher Lisa Bortolotti to pool thoughts about unintended consequences. (Photo: From left to right, Samuel Taylor Coleridge, a Xhosa warrior, Nelson Mandela. Credit: Getty Images) Show less